<theme id="thm220">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Compound time. 8th note tied to next beat</title>
<tocimage>img220.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson the next patterns are introduced:</para>

<score>
    <music>
    (score (vers 1.6)
      (instrument
        (musicData
        (time 6 8)
        (n * q)(n * e l)(n * q)(n * e)(barline double)
        (n * q. l)(n * e g+)(r e)(n * e g-)(barline end)
    )))
    </music>
</score>

<part>
<title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>

<score>
    <control_play />
    <control_measures />
    <music>
    (score (vers 1.6)
      (instrument
        (musicData
        (clef G)(key C)(time 6 8)
        (n a4 q)(n a4 e)(n a4 q)(n a4 e)(barline)
        (n a4 q)(n a4 e l)(n a4 q)(n a4 e)(barline)
        (n a4 q.)(n a4 e g+)(r e)(n a4 e g-)(barline)
        (n a4 q. l)(n a4 e g+)(r e)(n a4 e g-)(barline end)
    )))
    </music>
</score>
</part>

<part>
<title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm220_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear: 8th note tied to
next beat.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm220_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Train your ear: Dotted quarter note
tied to group of 8th note, 8th rest and 8th note.</para>
<para>
<link linkend="thm220_E3">Exercise 3</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>



</part>

